    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sun-dried-tomato-and-goats-cheese-fresh-orecchiette/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the grill to medium-high and boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sun-dried-tomato-and-goats-cheese-fresh-orecchiette/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>fresh orecchiette</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>orecchiette</strong> for 4-6 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>orecchiette</strong>, reserving a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Reboil a kettle</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sun-dried-tomato-and-goats-cheese-fresh-orecchiette/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and<strong> sun-dried tomatoes</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min</p><p>Add your <strong>flaked almonds</strong> to a baking tray and put the tray under the grill for 2-4 min or until toasted and lightly golden</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sun-dried-tomato-and-goats-cheese-fresh-orecchiette/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then add to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the <strong>wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong> until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can, then chop it roughly</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sun-dried-tomato-and-goats-cheese-fresh-orecchiette/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[195ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> to the pan with the sun-dried tomatoes and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sun-dried-tomato-and-goats-cheese-fresh-orecchiette/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, remove the pan from heat and add the <strong>drained orecchiette</strong>, <strong>chopped wilted spinach</strong> and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>goats' cheese</strong> (you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>to the pan</p><p>Give everything a gentle mix up until the cheese has melted and the pasta is coated in the sauce \u2013 this is your<strong> sun-dried tomato & goats' cheese fresh orecchiette</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sun-dried-tomato-and-goats-cheese-fresh-orecchiette/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sun-dried tomato & goats' cheese fresh orecchiette </strong>and crumble the <strong>remaining goats cheese</strong> over the top and season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Garnish with the<strong> toasted flaked almonds </strong>and drizzle everything with a little <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
